{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"gallant-communital-cub","creation_channel":"cli","description":"Follow-up discovered from 5e40. The deterministic trigger (unscoped attestation going stale-head on unrelated HEAD drift) is fixed in attest.compute_validity. RESIDUAL: when drift_refresh DOES escalate an unchanged plan to a full re-review, there is no deterministic Pass-3 convergence floor anchoring novel blocking findings to the prior signed verdict (repo data: 32% verdict instability on byte-identical plans). This is LLM-surface work requiring a behavioural eval (quantified threshold), not a unit test. Also note the separate crash-safe-stash defect recorded in 5e40's comments (review-plan attested-mode git stash/fetch not crash-safe).","id":"0916-8c47-6205-4a37","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"plan-review: drift-convergence Pass-3 floor for escalated unchanged-plan re-review (LLM-surface)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784495527127342001,"uuid":"9b141f5d-fac7-4a6a-88da-741f078e2ba6"}